      "side": 1,
      "message": "not for this CL.\n\nit occurred to me that we continue adding these filters directly to list requests, while we may have another RPC which also needs a generic filter like this.\n\nWill we ever need, say, an Update RPC that accepts a filter? e.g. if a whole VLAN is being turn down? Or, are hosts turned down incrementally in which case we don\u0027t need a massive-update-many-entities RPCs?\nRelated: BuildFilter message in go/buildbucket-api-v2 that is used in SearchBuilds and CancelBuilds RPCs\n\nWith filter messages (PhysicalHostFilter, MachineFilter) our messages would be shorter because they can reuse each other, e.g. instead of hosts and host_vlans fields we would have `PhysicalHostFilter hosts`. Also it would allow to filter by physical host state, too.\n\nIt is a API breaking change, so it would require a short period of downtime (or declaring v2, but it seems an overkill to me)",
      "revId": "7f6887cbe718ad90277dcb87afc67a8327ce5277",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "53810c70_bb3d8d4a",
        "filename": "machine-db/api/crimson/v1/vms.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 56,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-16T21:39:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think there might be some use cases for filters in Update, but it\u0027s probably rare. For example, right now we\u0027re debating whether to shorten one of the OS names. That involves adding the new OS to oses.cfg, updating all the hosts using the existing OS to point to the new one, then updating oses.cfg to remove the old OS. We could leverage filters to update all the hosts in one go, nut it\u0027s not that hard to script it one by one-- just takes a little longer.\n\nI\u0027m also wondering if maybe go/api-style\u0027s recommendation of a filter string is worth considering. The main downside is that it\u0027s harder to generate and interpret a filter string, but you don\u0027t need to modify the RPCs for each new filter and you can do comparisons like \u003c or \u003e (I need to add something to find hosts where the number of VMs \u003c VM slots, and there may be more use cases if/when we start adding physical properties of the machine like disk size, RAM, etc.).",
      "parentUuid": "980655bf_502775be",
      "revId": "7f6887cbe718ad90277dcb87afc67a8327ce5277",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
